<p>We will be using Node Affinity to keep the workload on the primary site at the start, only in case of downtime will the node shift towards any other site.</p>
<p>To apply Node Affinity, we first need to label our worker nodes.</p>
<ol>
 <li>
  <p>First, get the workers nodes by using the following command.</p>
 </li>
